4ï¸âƒ£ Longest Streak / Subarray / Window
ğŸ”’ Track last seen index to prevent repeats.

ğŸ§ª Example:

Find longest substring without repeating characters.

text
Copy
Edit
Input: "abcabcbb"
Output: 3  // "abc"
ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» Java Code:

java
Copy
Edit
Map<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
int left = 0, maxLen = 0;

for (int right = 0; right < s.length(); right++) {
    char c = s.charAt(right);
    if (map.containsKey(c)) {
        left = Math.max(left, map.get(c) + 1);
    }
    map.put(c, right);
    maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, right - left + 1);
}
ğŸ”— LeetCode: Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters â€“ #3

5ï¸âƒ£ Anagrams
ğŸ§  Group or compare strings with the same characters in any order.

ğŸ§ª Example:
Input: ["eat", "tea", "tan", "ate", "nat", "bat"]
Output: [["eat","tea","ate"],["tan","nat"],["bat"]]

ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» Java Code:

java
Copy
Edit
Map<String, List<String>> map = new HashMap<>();

for (String word : strs) {
    char[] chars = word.toCharArray();
    Arrays.sort(chars);
    String key = new String(chars);

    map.computeIfAbsent(key, k -> new ArrayList<>()).add(word);
}
return new ArrayList<>(map.values());
